    "Because of this, it is much better fitted for resource-constrained clinical environments.",
    "Moreover, the segmentation by the U-Net component outperforms traditional methods in delineating cancerous regions, as qualitatively understood from segmentation outputs [41] [42] [43] [44] [45] [46].",
    "Table 13; Fig. 20 shows the comparison between previous models.",
    "The PolyNetDWTCADx framework proved computationally efficient against the resource-intensive architectures of Vision Transformers.",
    "While these Vision Transformers are outstanding in feature representation for large-scale datasets, their performance largely depends on extensive computational resources and high-level hardware, making them unsuitable for medium-sized datasets such as CKHK-22."
